  "texts": [
    "Since X is vertical, its flow consists of bundle maps, and restricted to each fibre it is the flow of a nilsoliton.",
    "By Proposition A.4, the fibre restrictions are affine maps, thus the soliton is affine.",
    "Conversely, if (M, g, X) is an affine expanding soliton, then (g, X) satisfies Ansatz 3.1 by Theorem 6.2.",
    "Hence, we obtain a solution to the twisted harmonic-Einstein equation by Proposition 3.4.",
    "□To conclude this section, we now justify some claims made in the introduction.Proposition 6.3."
  ],
